block variations
  :markdown
    ### Horizontal

    `textarea` elements are not included in default styling of horizontal
    forms.

  form.form.form-horizontal
    .form_group
      label First Name
      input(type="text" placeholder="John")

    .form_group
      label Last Name
      input(type="text" placeholder="Smith")

    .form_group
      label Industry
      select
        option Academic
        option Automotive
        option Finance
        option Government
        option Medical
        option Restaurant
        option Technology

    input(type="submit" role="button")

  .if-semantic
    :markdown
      Both the `form()` and `form_group()` mixins need to pass in `horizontal`
      as a parameter. This is because it is possible to have a vertical
      form with both horizontal and vertical form groups

          <form>
            <div class="group">
              <label for="fname">First name</label>
              <input name="fname" type="text" />
            </div>
            <div class="group">
              <label for="lname">Last name</label>
              <input name="lname" type="text" />
            </div>
            <div class="group">
              <label for="industry">Industry</label>
              <select name="industry">
                ...
              </select>
            </div>
            <input type="submit" />
          </form>

          form {
            @include form('horizontal');
          }
          .group {
            @include form_group('horizontal');
          }

  .ifnot-semantic
    :markdown
      Simply add `.form-horizontal` to `.form` to convert to a horizontal form.

          <form class="form form-horizontal">
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="fname">First name</label>
              <input name="fname" type="text" />
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="lname">Last name</label>
              <input name="lname" type="text" />
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="industry">Industry</label>
              <select name="industry">
                ...
              </select>
            </div>
            <input type="submit" />
          </form>

  :markdown
    ### Left-aligned

    For left-aligned forms, simply use the grid.
    
    - Add `row` to the `form_group`
    - Add column styles to labels
    - Either put inputs and text fields in column elements
      or apply column styling directly.

  form.form.form-left
    .form_group.row
      label.col-third First Name
      .col-twothirds
        input(type="text" placeholder="John")

    .form_group.row
      label.col-third Last Name
      .col-twothirds
        input(type="text" placeholder="Smith")

    .form_group.row
      label.col-third Bio
      .col-twothirds
        textarea

    .form_group.row
      label.checkbox.col-third.col-left-third
        input(type="checkbox")
        |  Sign up for newsletter

    .form_group.row
      label.col-third Industry
      .col-twothirds
        select
          option Academic
          option Automotive
          option Finance
          option Government
          option Medical
          option Restaurant
          option Technology

    .row
      .col-third.col-left-third
        input.button.button-primary(type="submit" role="button")

